This paper is about deep neural network compression, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a method for training a quantized DNN that improves accuracy. The paper also uses image datasets, which suggests that it could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves training neural networks, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves compression, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
